# Design Elements Commonality

Pragmatic UI standards that prioritize readability and user efficiency over decorative complexity.

---

## 1. Structural Hierarchy (Anti-Nesting)

**Goal**: Minimize "box under box" nesting. Use flat layouts with clear visual grouping.

| Approach | ✅ Do | ❌ Avoid |
|----------|-------|----------|
| Container depth | 2 levels max (page → card/section) | 3+ nested borders |
| Grouping | Spacing, subtle borders (`border-b`), background tints | Multiple nested cards |
| Separation | `divide-y`, `gap-6`, `py-4` | `border` wrapping every sub-element |
| Elevation | Single shadow level, subtle | Stacked shadows creating depth illusion |

**Progressive Disclosure**: Show summary info inline; hide details behind expand/collapse or secondary views. Don't put complex forms inside cards inside cards.

```tsx
// ✅ Flat section with divider grouping
<div className="space-y-6">
  <section>
    <h3 className="text-sm font-medium mb-3">Team Configuration</h3>
    <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      {/* Cards are siblings, not nested */}
    </div>
  </section>
  <hr className="border-border" />
  <section>
    <h3 className="text-sm font-medium mb-3">Preferences</h3>
    {/* Content */}
  </section>
</div>

// ❌ Deep nesting
<Card><CardContent>
  <Card><CardContent>
    <Card><CardContent>...</CardContent></Card>
  </CardContent></Card>
</CardContent></Card>
```

