## 5. Dialog Width

| Content Type | Width | Notes |
|--------------|-------|-------|
| Standard forms, confirmations | `max-w-lg` (512px) | Default for most dialogs |
| Tables, wide forms, side-by-side | `max-w-2xl` or `max-w-4xl` | Only when content genuinely needs space |
| Wizards, multi-step | `max-w-2xl` | Consistent width across steps |

Always allow text wrapping. Never force single-line text that truncates.

```tsx
// ✅ Default (most dialogs)
<DialogContent className="max-w-lg">
  <p className="text-xs text-muted-foreground">
    Instruction text that wraps naturally
  </p>
</DialogContent>

// ✅ Wide (only for tables/large forms)
<DialogContent className="max-w-2xl max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto">
  {/* Wide content */}
</DialogContent>
```

